subSubSection.paragraph:
Collophore (
Fig. 11G
). Anterior side with 15 chaetae, basally 7 spine-like chaetae, 1 thin mic, 2 inner mic and 2 long ciliate chaetae apically acuminate, distally with 2 mac and 1 long ciliate chaetae apically acuminate (as in 
Fig. 6E
); posterior side distally with 4 chaetae per side, 3 reduced spine and 1 ciliate chaeta; lateral flap with 5 smooth and 14 ciliate chaetae.

Furcula (
Fig. 11H
). Manubrium ventrally with formula 1, 2, 2, 2/4 (subapical), 18 (apical) ciliate chaetae and approximately 18 elongated apical scales per side; manubrial plate with 8 ciliate chaetae of different sizes and 3 psp (as in 
Fig. 6G
). Furcula lacking blunt chaetae.

